Using Chebyshev's inequality, for a random variable \( X \) with mean \( \mu \) and variance \( \sigma^2 \), \( P(|X - \mu| \geq c) \leq \sigma^2 / c^2 \), so \( P(|X - \mu| < c) \geq 1 - \sigma^2 / c^2 \).

