- The blood pressure categories (high, normal, low) must sum to 100%, so P(normal BP) = 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.  
- 17% have an irregular heartbeat, so P(irregular HB) = 17%.  
- Of those with irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so P(high BP and irregular HB) = 35% × 17% = 5.95%.  
