Problem: A doctor is concerned about the relationship between blood pressure and irregular heartbeats. Among her patients, she classifies blood pressures as high, normal, or low and heartbeats as regular or irregular and finds that 16\% have high blood pressure; (b) 19\% have low blood pressure; (c) $17 \%$ have an irregular heartbeat; (d) of those with an irregular heartbeat, $35 \%$ have high blood pressure; and (e) of those with normal blood pressure, $11 \%$ have an irregular heartbeat. What percentage of her patients have a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure? The unit of the answer should be % .
Solution: To find the percentage of patients with a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure, the given information is used step by step.

- 16% have high blood pressure, so P(high BP) = 16%.  
- 19% have low blood pressure, so P(low BP) = 19%.  
- The blood pressure categories (high, normal, low) must sum to 100%, so P(normal BP) = 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.  
- 17% have an irregular heartbeat, so P(irregular HB) = 17%.  
- Of those with irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so P(high BP and irregular HB) = 35% × 17% = 5.95%.  
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have irregular heartbeat, so P(normal BP and irregular HB) = 11% × 65% = 7.15%.  

The total irregular heartbeat cases must account for all blood pressure categories:  
P(irregular HB) = P(high BP and irregular HB) + P(normal BP and irregular HB) + P(low BP and irregular HB).  
Thus, P(low BP and irregular HB) = P(irregular HB) - P(high BP and irregular HB) - P(normal BP and irregular HB) = 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.  

Patients with low blood pressure can have either regular or irregular heartbeat:  
P(low BP) = P(low BP and regular HB) + P(low BP and irregular HB).  
Therefore, P(low BP and regular HB) = P(low BP) - P(low BP and irregular HB) = 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.  

The result is 15.10%, which is rounded to one decimal place as 15.1% for consistency with the input percentages, which are given as whole numbers or with one decimal place in intermediate steps.

